37096>>>>>    Function IsLoggedIn Returns Boolean
37098>>>>>        String sLoginName
37098>>>>>        Boolean bLogWebSession bLoggedIn
37098>>>>>        
37098>>>>>        Get pbLogWebSession to bLogWebSession
37099>>>>>        If not bLogWebSession Begin
37101>>>>>            Forward Get IsLoggedIn to bLoggedIn
37103>>>>>            Function_Return bLoggedIn
37104>>>>>        End
37104>>>>>>
37104>>>>>        
37104>>>>>        Get psLoginName to sLoginName
37105>>>>>        
37105>>>>>        Function_Return (sLoginName <> "")
37106>>>>>    End_Function
37107>>>>>    
37107>>>>>    
37107>>>>>    //
37107>>>>>    // This procedure is called when validating a session and after logging in. Its purpose is to 
37107>>>>>    // update properties based on the session and user data. Augment this function to update 
37107>>>>>    // properties based on the session / user table. Note that WebAppUser and WebAppSession contain
37107>>>>>    // the right records when this procedure is called.
37107>>>>>    //
37107>>>>>    // Params:
37107>>>>>    //      bClear   True if the procedure is called before session validation to clear properties.
37107>>>>>    //
37107>>>>>    Procedure UpdateSessionProperties Boolean bClear
37109>>>>>        Handle hoUserDD
37109>>>>>        
37109>>>>>        Get phoUserDD to hoUserDD
37110>>>>>        
37110>>>>>        //  Update user properties
37110>>>>>        If (not(bClear) and HasRecord(hoUserDD)) Begin
37112>>>>>            Set psUsername to (Trim(WebAppUser.FullName))
37113>>>>>            Set psLoginName to (Trim(WebAppUser.LoginName))
37114>>>>>            Set piUserRights to WebAppUser.Rights
37115>>>>>            
37115>>>>>            Send OnSessionPropertiesSet 
37116>>>>>        End
37116>>>>>>
37116>>>>>        Else Begin
37117>>>>>            Set psUsername to ""
37118>>>>>            Set psLoginName to ""
37119>>>>>            Set piUserRights to 0
37120>>>>>            
37120>>>>>            Send OnSessionPropertiesClear
37121>>>>>        End
37121>>>>>>
37121>>>>>    End_Procedure
37122>>>>>    
37122>>>>>    Procedure OnSessionPropertiesSet
37124>>>>>        //  Empty event stub
37124>>>>>    End_Procedure
37125>>>>>    
37125>>>>>    Procedure OnSessionPropertiesClear
37127>>>>>        //  Empty event stub
37127>>>>>    End_Procedure
37128>>>>>    
37128>>>>>    Procedure EndSession
37130>>>>>        Integer iErr
37130>>>>>        Boolean bLogWebSession
37130>>>>>        Handle hoSessionDD       
37130>>>>>        
37130>>>>>        Get phoSessionDD to hoSessionDD
37131>>>>>        Get pbLogWebSession to bLogWebSession
37132>>>>>        If not bLogWebSession Begin
37134>>>>>            Forward Send EndSession
37136>>>>>            Procedure_Return
37137>>>>>        End
37137>>>>>>
37137>>>>>            
37137>>>>>        //  Check if session exists
37137>>>>>        Send Clear of hoSessionDD
37138>>>>>        Get psSessionKey to WebAppSession.SessionKey
37139>>>>>        
37139>>>>>        Send Find of hoSessionDD EQ Index.1
37140>>>>>        If (Found) Begin
37142>>>>>            Set Field_Changed_Value of hoSessionDD Field WebAppSession.Active to "N"
37143>>>>>            Get Request_Validate of hoSessionDD to iErr
37144>>>>>            If (iErr) Begin
37146>>>>>                // this should not happen. If it does its a programming error
37146>>>>>                Error DFERR_PROGRAM C_$WebAppSessionValidateFailed
37147>>>>>>
37147>>>>>                Procedure_Return
37148>>>>>            End
37148>>>>>>
37148>>>>>            Send Request_Save of hoSessionDD
37149>>>>>        End
37149>>>>>>
37149>>>>>    End_Procedure
37150>>>>>
37150>>>>>End_Class
37151>>>>>
